						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up at the entrance of the temple.</p>						

						<p>7th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription can be assigned to the 7th century A.D. on the basis of palaeography and internal evidences.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of <hi rend="italic">pannasa</hi> by Eṟigal Dugarāju to a brāhmin <hi rend="italic">(pāṟa)</hi> [Rē*]vaśarmma, belonging to Kochchiya (Kauśika gōtra) while Chōḷamahārāju was ruling from Urugaṭūru (present Uruṭūru) ?</p>						

						<p>The record was engraved by certain Asivairuvu.</p>						

						<p>(Pub. <hi rend="italic">Epigraphia Indica.</hi> Vol. XXVII, pp 229 ff.)</p>						

						</summary>
